'''Mandalorian Supercommandos''', or '''''Mando Ori'ramikade''''' in [[Mando'a/Legends|Mando'a]], were a subculture of the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorians]] that followed the [[Supercommando Codex]], as written by [[Jaster Mereel]], conducting themselves as highly paid soldiers and honorable mercenaries. They emulated the combat training of the original Supercommandos that were formed by and modeled after [[Mandalore the Indomitable]].

==History==
===Republic Era===
In [[60 BBY/Legends|60 BBY]], [[Mandalore (title)/Legends|Mandalore]] [[Jaster Mereel]] issued his [[Supercommando Codex]]. Jaster's men served as mercenaries and warriors for hire,<ref name="GaW">''[[Galaxy at War]]''</ref> but their primary goal was to hunt the [[Death Watch/Legends|Death Watch]].<ref name="OpenSeasons1">[[Jango Fett: Open Seasons 1|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'' 1]]</ref><ref name="OpenSeasons2">[[Jango Fett: Open Seasons 2|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'' 2]]</ref> During the [[Mandalorian Civil War (True Mandalorians)|Mandalorian Civil War]], the Supercommandos loyal to Mereel's [[True Mandalorians|True Mandalorian]] faction were eliminated to the last man at the [[Battle of Galidraan]] in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]].<ref name="OpenSeasons3">[[Jango Fett: Open Seasons 3|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'' 3]]</ref> Following the war, many Supercommandos traveled throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] as [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]].<ref name="HotM">{{InsiderCite|80|The History of the Mandalorians: Exploring the Evolution of a Mighty Race of Warriors}}</ref>

====Clone Wars====
Decades later, during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Spar|Mandalore the Resurrector]] and [[Fenn Shysa]] trained a battalion of Supercommandos that raided Republic holdings as Separatist hired mercenaries.<ref name="GaW">''[[Galaxy at War]]''</ref> By the end of the war, a large number of Supercommandos, including those of the [[Mandalorian Protectors (Spar)|Mandalorian Protectors]], had been killed in action.<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>

===Post-Imperial Era===
By the time of the [[Second Galactic Civil War]] in [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], Mandalore [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] had a total of one hundred Supercommandos to call on, including Fett's granddaughter [[Mirta Gev]], her fiancé [[Ghes Orade]], Orade's adoptive father [[Novoc Vevut]], [[Baltan Carid]], [[Ram Zerimar]], and [[Goran Beviin]].

During the [[Second Battle of Fondor]], Fett led a group of fifty Supercommandos allied with [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala]] aboard the [[Turbulent-class Star Destroyer|''Turbulent''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Bloodfin (Star Destroyer)|''Bloodfin'']] to retake the ship from forces loyal to the [[Moff/Legends|Moffs]] attempting to join forces with [[Darth Caedus]]. The Commandos succeeded, although they were forced to allow [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] [[Tahiri Veila]] to escape with aid from Caedus due to Fett's orders that only [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] could confront her brother.<ref name="Revelation">''[[Legacy of the Force: Revelation]]''</ref>

